MBOMBELA &#8211; A driver escaped death when the rear of her car was hit by a truck at the intersection of Old Pretoria Road and Devland Cash and Carry this afternoon.Traffic was affected as police maintained order on the busy road.Also read: Passenger dead and passenger critical after car accident The woman was unharmed, but was treated for shock by ER24. She said everything happened incredibly quickly. &#8220;I was indicating so that I can turn to the shopping complex when I suddenly saw a truck coming from the back. It happened so fast and fortunately I was wearing a seat belt,&#8221; she said.Also read: 10 people killed in minibus accident As a result of the impact, the rear of her car was totally crushed. The truck driver was also unharmed.Also read: Three killed in accident on R38